  section#grid-object
    h2 The Grid Object
    p.
      The Grid Object is similar to the Flex Object except that it can be extended
      to two dimensions.
      It has the structure of a list in that all items share the same container
      (unlike tables where cells might not share the same row), while at the same time
      appearing like a table with rows and columns.
    p.
      By default, each item has a #[b main size] of 100%.
      This behavior can be overridden with the
      #[code.x-code flex] or
      #[code.x-code flex-basis] properties.
      Using media queries, you can achieve a flexible and responsive table effect,
      adjusting the number of #[b cross axes]&mdash;columns if
      #[code.x-code flex-direction: row;], or rows if
      #[code.x-code flex-direction: column;]&mdash;based on screen size.
      In order to appear like a table, all the items within
      a #[b cross axis] should have the same #[b main size].
